The paper deals with denoising 3D point clouds, which is a problem commonly encountered in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of 3D point clouds is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and augmented reality (cs.AR). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves smoothing and averaging, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
